    "attributes": {
        "action": "Government to amend rules so GPs can charge Solicitors for postage for SAR.",
        "additional_details": "Historically practices could charge up to \u00a350.00 to cover the consumables and postage charges. \r\nSolicitors are requesting information under a SAR request despite it clearly being for litigation. Patients are consenting to full medical records which under data protection is excessive in line with the Caldecott principals.\r\n",
        "background": "GDPR has put a financial burden of \u00a325 for postage on GP Practices for Subject Access Requests (SAR) for litigation cases from Solicitors. Solicitors are capitalising on this as opposed to requesting Access To Medical Records which carries a fee. GP time to remove sensitive data is not recoverable.",
